This paper is primarily focused on improving the robustness of deep neural networks against adversarial attacks in the context of visual classification. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new defense technique that involves attention maps and logit pairing, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new defense technique that involves optimizing the activations of the model, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category.
